\f0\fs24 \cf0 Reading Notes Web App\
\
Feature requirement - add LLM summarization logic for voice recording notes\
\
User Story:\
When i use the voice recording feature to recall what i\'92ve read in a book, the transcript text often gets messy and incoherent due to two reasons: 1) i ramble when i speak and 2) the speech-to-text api makes mistakes in translating due to low voice/noisy background or bad pronunciation. These tend to be uncontrollable factors (#1 can be improved as i practice speaking more) and make it hard for me to revisit these voice notes in the future when i want to recall ideas from the book.\
\
Requirement:\
\
user flow #1 - LLM bullet point summarization; entry points\
After completing each voice recording, i will be offered to summarize my text using AI. when opting in, the app will consume the raw transcript and feed into an LLM, producing a concise, crisp summary *only* in non-verbose bullet points.\
\
if i choose to opt out, i can always trigger the LLM summarization API later on for each voice note id\
\
