\cf0 user flow #2 - New tab under each voice note id\
afterwards, the LLM output will be saved under each voice note id. UI-wise, when i click a voice note id, it will show the raw transcript in one tab (Existing) and the LLM-summarized points in another tab (New addition).\
\
this tab will be empty if the user hasn\'92t triggered the LLM summary API\
\
user flow #3 - LLM title summary\
Currently the latest raw transcript will be shown under each voice note card and book card. regardless of LLM summarization status, always convert the raw transcript into a 10-word maximum title shown in the voice note and book card. this will be a separate prompt to the LLM summarization}